<BYLINE>
   By BRUCE JACQUES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SYDNEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE BOARD of Western Mining Corporation, the Australian metals producer, has
taken the rare step of publicly disciplining the company's managing
director, Mr Hugh Morgan, over the loss of a mining lease earlier this year.
The disciplinary action was announced yesterday by Sir Arvi Parbo, WMC
chairman, following an internal inquiry into the loss of the mining lease,
known as Ernest Henry, which is expected to reduce the company's annual
earnings by ADollars 20m (USDollars 13.50m).
