</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
BELL CANADA, the eastern Canada telecommunications utility and main income
contributor to BCE, Canada's biggest telecommunications group, says it will
make a sweeping review of its business after losing a bid to raise local
telephone rates by an average of 10 per cent, writes Robert Gibbens in
Montreal.
Bell argued before the Canadian Radio-Television and Telecommunications
Commission that it needed CDollars 315m (USDollars 238m) more revenues in
