revenues lost to long distance competition. For many years long distance
rates have subsidised local rates.
But the CRTC, the federal regulator, said Bell did not need the increases to
retain 'financial integrity'. It reduced the company's allowable rate of
return to 11 to 12 per cent from 12.5 to 13.5 per cent sought by Bell.
