FT  01 SEP 93 / Computers near higher intelligence
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
JAPANESE scientists are set to develop a machine as intelligent as a cat in
the next five to six years. This will pave the way for computers more
intelligent than humans, according to Professor Kevin Warwick of the
University of Reading's cybernetics department.
'Technically we know that certain aspects of human intelligence such as
memory, decision-making and logic, can not only be artificially replicated
but in fact the artificial form is much faster, more powerful, more flexible
and more reliable,' he said.
