FT  01 SEP 93 / Greenhouse effect forecast worsens
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
RESEARCH SHOWS that plants growing in a future 'greenhouse effect'
atmosphere will release less water vapour than previously predicted. This
means that the earth would become drier, with reduced cloud formation and
lower rainfall.
The finding is in the first report of the Terrestrial Initiative in Global
Environmental Research, launched in 1991.
