<HEADLINE>
FT  01 SEP 93 / World Trade News: US may lift missile sanctions
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NANCY DUNNE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE US is willing to negotiate lifting sanctions worth Dollars 500m-Dollars
1bn (Pounds 660m) imposed last week on China and Pakistan over the sale of
components of M-11 missiles, according to a senior State Department
official, Nancy Dunne writes from Washington.
Mr Winston Lord, assistant US secretary of state for Asia and the Pacific,
yesterday said he was prepared to give China, which sold the components to
Pakistan, another chance because there were areas in the guidelines to the
Missiles Technology Control Regime that contained 'possible ambiguity'.
China, he pointed out, had consistently denied violating the MTCR, to which
it is not a signatory.
