<HEADLINE>
FT  01 SEP 93 / The Middle East: Self-rule timetable
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE plan for Palestinian self-rule foresees a permanent accord based on
Israeli withdrawal from occupied lands, according to versions of the draft
text, AP reports.
An elected Palestinian council would govern Jericho and Gaza for a
transitional period of no more than five years. The council will have some
legislative powers, and would be elected within nine months after the
agreement takes effect. A permanent accord would follow.
Within two months of the agreement becoming effective the two sides will
sign a deal on withdrawal of Israeli troops from populated Palestinian areas
in Gaza and Jericho, to be completed within four months. Talks on the
permanent status of the territories are to start no later than the beginning
of the third year of the interim period.
</TEXT>
